{
  "stem": "24212.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not that they would dovetail into our story, no.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, when the war began, in Europe, I was 12 or 13.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I remember anger.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I saw-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] a few months before the war started, I saw the German army march into my country.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it was heartbreaking.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was very heartbreaking, because all these ideals that we grew up with-- freedom, truth shall prevail-- all that went down the drain, you know, first of all by the treacherous behavior of the-- of France and England, who sold Czechoslovakia down the river at Munich.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They sold out.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Treaty, no treaty, you know.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And so it was a very bitter moment.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] But life went on.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we still went skiing.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we still were swimming around.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But it was very sad.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not really, because as I said before, I wasn't politically active.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And so I didn't give political speeches also.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And if we were cursing the Germans, we cursed the Germans in our closed company of friends, where just about everybody had the same feelings.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But you had to start to watch your mouth when you were in public, let's say in a coffee house, or at intermission in a movie, because you never knew who stands next to you and might report you that you said that Hitler is an idiot or some grandiose statement like that.",
      "word_count": 53
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Most of them that I remember got sick to their stomachs, because evidently when they came to Czechoslovakia, they saw for the first time in a long time whip cream or-- or good chocolate or what have you.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they just overate.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the hospitals were full of German soldiers who had their stomachs pumped out, at which point, of course, we rejoiced.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
